title: Old Barn Window Matted Framed Art by Lois Bryan with Black Frame, 16 by 20-Inch
description: This matted framed art piece features a window covered in vines.

"My images are based on the photographs I capture, mostly with Nikon cameras and lenses. Although my primary goal will always be to catch that perfect shot straight out of the camera, I also enjoy tinkering around in Photoshop and other image editing programs. I don't have one particular style and probably never will. I'm pretty much all over the place with what catches my interest. [I'm] still experimenting, still loving every minute behind the camera and still believing in the magic." -Lois Byran.
An 11x14 giclee print under acrylic in a 16x20 black frame. Giclee (jee-clay) is an advanced printmaking process for creating museum quality fine art reproductions.

This high quality print is matted using antique white matting and comes in a black frame. A clear acrylic facing is added to protect the print. The piece is fully assembled by professional frames and comes ready to hang. The antique white mat allows the image to really stand out, making it a great addition to any space.
